title: Add larger Wear specific action icons.
message:
Add larger Wear specific action icons.

The default notification action icon size is 48dp (32dp optical). However, those icons appear blurry on Android Wear devices as they expect 64dp (48 optical) sized action icons. By using WearableExtender, we specify the larger Wear icons for those actions. Note: we cannot use the same icon for both as the notification tray does NOT scale down the icons to 48dp so they appear much too large.

title: Update list empty state with progress spinner pre-load, image+text if no contractions
message:
Update list empty state with progress spinner pre-load, image+text if no contractions

Previously, the empty state was a single line of unstyled text saying 'Loading Contractions' prior to the first cursor being returned, then nothing after that except the Average bar and the column headers (exactly what isn't helpful).

Now, the prior to first load shows an indeterminate progress spinner (for all of the 1/4 second it is there) before fading into the new empty state: a light gray image and instructions to 'Breathe'. In all cases, the Averages bar and column headers remain hidden until there is at least one contraction - when the first contraction is added, both nicely animate into view.

Note that the image is a placeholder image at this point - a future commit will replace it with the actual image

title: Moves Export/Import actions from menu to own Preferences section
message:
Moves Export/Import actions from menu to own Preferences section

Export and Import actions were not discoverable in the overflow menu. This makes them high level elements in the Settings screen and moves their logic into their own Activities rather than being embedded in the Preferences activity.

message: Fixes misnamed ic_dialog_alert

message: Adds missing dialog alert icon

title: Removes unnecessary Settings section dividers
message:
Removes unnecessary Settings section dividers

Per Settings Design (http://developer.android.com/design/patterns/settings.html), you should only add a section divider when there are greater than 7 settings in total. Previously, we had sections with only one preference in them! Combines all of the smaller settings while spliting out non-functionality (Analytics, open source licenses, about) into separate 'Other' section.

title: Adds warning icon to Reset dialog, improves message
message: Adds warning icon to Reset dialog, improves message

title: Update strings to sentence case to match Android writing style
message: Update strings to sentence case to match Android writing style

title: Ensure reset button only disables when there are no contractions at all
message:
Ensure reset button only disables when there are no contractions at all

Previously, the reset button was disabled if there were no contractions within the current average time span. This unfortunately made it impossible to delete those contractions without starting a new contraction. This splits the Reset menu item and the data it relies on into a separate headless fragment which looks at all available contractions in order to set the enabled/disabled state properly.

title: Load Google Play license info asynchronously
message:
Load Google Play license info asynchronously

Google Play license info is huge and loading it in onCreate caused a significant delay in opening LicenseActivity so load it asynchronously to improve responsiveness.

title: Lint suggested cleanup
message: Lint suggested cleanup

title: Hide Share button until there is valid data to share
message:
Hide Share button until there is valid data to share

Rather than disable (making the button visible but unclickable), hide the share button when there is no valid data. Lack of disabled feedback left the share button feeling broken.

title: Ensure KEYSTORE environment variable exists before attempting to read it as the keystore file
message:
Ensure KEYSTORE environment variable exists before attempting to read it as the keystore file

This allows other developers to checkout the project and build it successfully even if they do not have the KEYSTORE set up properly to build a release build (something they wouldn't do anyways).

title: Combines Share, promotes to Action Bar
message:
Combines Share, promotes to Action Bar

Previously, only the reset action appeared on the Action Bar. Given the additional work that has gone into Export Contractions (more to be done as well), the Share All is less useful now. Therefore we can raise the prominance of the single share action to the Action Bar.

Due to space constraints, only show the reset button when screen width>450dp (i.e., normal phones in landscape, tablets).

Reset button also becomes disabled if there are no contractions and enable status is now updated when the underlying data changes.

title: Adds open source license activity
message:
Adds open source license activity

Ensures that all open source libraries used are properly attributed

title: Moves About screen to Preferences
message:
Moves About screen to Preferences

About is not important enough to be in the main overflow menu. This moves it from a DialogFragment triggered from the overflow to an option in the Settings screen which launches a DialogWhenLarge activity to view About information

message:
Set an alarm to update the notification after first start time + average time frame amount of time

This ensures that if no contraction has started since then (likely, otherwise we would have been called in the mean time) there will be no contractions within the average time period and the notification will be cancelled automatically

title: As ongoing notifications do not show up on Android Wear, make notification never ongoing.
message:
As ongoing notifications do not show up on Android Wear, make notification never ongoing.

Previously, the notification would not update when toggling the contraction as the 'timing contraction' mode was ongoing and hence would not be written to Android Wear

message: Adds analytics for launching MainActivity from the notification's content intent

title: Ensure Add/Edit Note action opens UI when using notification action
message:
Ensure Add/Edit Note action opens UI when using notification action

The notification shade does not close unless you are using PendingIntent.getActivity so we need to route through NoteTransparentActivity (which now only shows saving note Toast if there is voice input). As EditActivity is not reachable for ongoing contractions, we instead use MainActivity's NoteDialogFragment to show the note input UI.

Required some rework of analytics (specifically Launch taking a 'type' parameter) to take into account launching from either Add or Edit Note Notification Action.

message:
Adds 'Add Note'/'Edit Note' notification action with Android Wear voice input

Also:
- Shrinks 'Start Contraction'/'Stop Contraction' actions to just use start/stop as there was not enough space to see the entire label
 - Updates notification action icons to use ic_notif_action to distinguish them from action bar icons (ic_action)
 - Minor code cleanup relating to checking if there is an existing note

title: Fixes inverted check
message:
Fixes inverted check

Don't show the notification if we can't move to the first element

title: Re-arrange notification building code
message:
Re-arrange notification building code

Rather than going through the entire cursor then back to the beginning, we get the information we need about the current contraction (ongoing status, etc) before iterating through the remaining contractions. This also fixes an issue where we would miss contractions in our averages calculations. Also updates some comments to be more clear on why we are doing certain operations.

title: Splits Averages onto second page for Android Wear devices.
message:
Splits Averages onto second page for Android Wear devices.

As we use setUsesChronometer(true), the bigText does not show on the main page on Android Wear devices. Therefore we split the averages onto a second page so that they are visible.

title: Adds notification tracking current contraction
message:
Adds notification tracking current contraction

Only shows if there is a contraction within the average time frame (as per settings). If the current contraction is ongoing, then the notification is also set to ongoing (i.e., not cancelable) and a 'Stop Contraction' action is available. Otherwise, it is dismissable and shows a 'Start Contraction' action. Uses the chronometer feature to show a count up time of the current duration (for ongoing) or frequency (non-ongoing).

title: Fixes improper task stack when opening from the Control Widget.
message:
Fixes improper task stack when opening from the Control Widget.

Previously, multiple instances of the MainActivity could be created and
would have separate back stacks associated with them. Also, if the user
was in a dialog/preference page, it would appear when you clicked on the
app launch in the Control Widget. Now, there is only one instance of the
MainActivity and it closes all activities/dialogs on top of it when
opening from the Control Widget.

title: Refactors all access to Analytics to AnalyticsManagerService.
message:
Refactors all access to Analytics to AnalyticsManagerService.

As all Analytics methods write directly to a SQL database (with no
background processing 150-450ms each), I encapsulated all of those
methods into the AnalyticsManagerService IntentService, which then runs
them on a worker thread. This significantly reduces the lag associated
with performing any action.
